<doc id="176383" wikidata="Q2928395" url="?curid=176383" title="Privy Council Office (United Kingdom)">
<text>The Privy Council Office (PCO) provides secretariat and administrative support to the Lord President of the Council in his or her capacity as president of His Majesty&#x27;s Most Honourable Privy Council. The head of the office is the Clerk of the Privy Council. The PCO is an independent unit based in the Cabinet Office.

