<doc id="176407" wikidata="Q3533298" url="?curid=176407" title="Pile hitch">
<text>The pile hitch is a kind of hitch, which is a knot used for attaching rope to a pole or other structure. The pile hitch is very easy to tie and can be tied in the bight, without access to either end of the rope, making it a valuable tool.

== Tying ==
To tie, form a loop in the bight, and wrap both strands of this loop around the pole near the pole&#x27;s end. Pull the loop around and under the rope, then finish by putting the loop itself around the end of the pole.
==See also==
*List of knots

